            . I am a carpenter in <placeName id="t18080713-28-crimeloc180">Little Guildford street, Russel square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18080713-28-crimeloc180" type="placeName" value="Little Guildford street, Russel square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18080713-28-crimeloc180" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18080713-28-off178 t18080713-28-crimeloc180"></join>. On Saturday the 18th of June we observed Richardson walking about the premises before twelve o'clock; we watched him. About six o'clock at night we observed the prisoner Keefe walking round the premises; in about five minutes he returned with Richardson; Richardson went into the coach house and took the deals, Keefe walking on to Torrington street; Richards took the deals on his shoulder, carrying them towards Torrington street; I and another man took him in Torrington street, and we stopped Keefe at the same time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18080713-28-person333">
                  GEORGE 
                  RILEY
